        <h2 class="c-heading c-heading--2 u-mb-16">Why MIND?</h2>
        <p class="u-mb-16">
          Most languages treat tensors, autodiff, and ML compilation as external libraries.
          <strong>MIND</strong> bakes them into the language core, so you can reason about models
          as first-class programs – not as opaque framework graphs.
        </p>
        <ul class="c-list c-list--check u-mb-0">
          <li><strong>First-class tensors</strong> with shape &amp; dtype types.</li>
          <li><strong>Reverse-mode autodiff</strong> integrated into the evaluator.</li>
          <li><strong>MLIR execution</strong> for interpreters, JIT, CPU backends, and AOT builds.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="o-layout__item u-1/2@md">
